Use `hull()` to compute the smallest interval that contains both time windows. In your case:

```aiken
let deadline_allowed = between(1000, 5000)
let extension_window = between(4500, 6000)
let combined = hull(deadline_allowed, extension_window)
// Result: between(1000, 6000)
```

The `hull()` function merges the two intervals into a single interval spanning from the earliest lower bound (1000) to the latest upper bound (6000). This is useful when you need to validate that a transaction timestamp falls within any of several acceptable time ranges—the hull gives you the outer boundary of all valid times.

Note: If the intervals are disjoint (don't overlap and don't touch), `hull()` still computes the smallest interval that would contain both, filling in any gap between them.

