    let multiplied = factor * some_script_size
    multiplied
  }
  None -> {
    // The factor was not set in this protocol update
    0
  }
}
```

The returned `Rational` value is a multiplicative factor that applies to reference scripts. Since reference scripts become more expensive every ~24KB tier, this initial factor serves as the base coefficient that grows exponentially with each subsequent tier. You'll typically use this when calculating the cost of executing reference scripts under new protocol parameters.

