use cardano/transaction.{ScriptPurpose, Mint}
use cardano/transaction/script_purpose

pub fn validate_purposes(purpose1: ScriptPurpose, purpose2: ScriptPurpose) -> Bool {
  let ordering = script_purpose.compare(purpose1, purpose2)
  when ordering is {
    Less -> True
    Equal -> True
    Greater -> False
  }
}
```

The `compare` function takes two `ScriptPurpose` values and returns an `Ordering` type (Less, Equal, or Greater). It handles all script purpose variants: `Mint`, `Spend`, `Withdraw`, `Vote`, `Propose`, and `Publish`.

For `Mint` purposes, it compares the underlying byte arrays. The function uses `bytearray.compare()` internally for byte-level comparison, ensuring consistent and deterministic ordering across different purpose types.

Puedes usar la función `compare` del módulo `cardano/transaction/script_purpose` para validar el orden entre dos `ScriptPurpose`. Aquí está un ejemplo práctico:

