- **beneficiary: VerificationKeyHash** – The hash of the beneficiary's verification key. This is the account permitted to claim the funds once lock_until is reached.

The type is public (`pub`) so it can be imported and used in other modules. VerificationKeyHash is imported from aiken/crypto and represents a cryptographic identifier on Cardano. When a transaction attempts to spend this UTXO, the validator receives this datum and can pattern-match on its fields to enforce time and signature constraints.

