    _self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    let updated = list.push(redeemer, policy_id)
    !list.is_empty(updated)
  }
}
```

Since `list.push` always produces a list with at least one element (the newly prepended `policy_id`), the `!list.is_empty` check will always be `True` here — but the pattern demonstrates how to accumulate policy ids across redeemer data.

