You can construct a closed interval [1, 10] by building the `Interval` struct directly with `IntervalBound` values:

```aiken
use aiken/interval.{Interval, IntervalBound, IntervalBoundType}

let i: Interval =
  Interval {
    lower_bound: IntervalBound { bound_type: Finite(1), is_inclusive: True },
    upper_bound: IntervalBound { bound_type: Finite(10), is_inclusive: True },
