You can use `bytearray.push/2` from `aiken/primitive/bytearray` to add a byte at the front of a `ByteArray`.

```aiken
use aiken/primitive/bytearray

// Prepend 0x01 to an existing ByteArray
let result = bytearray.push(#"0203", 1)
// result == #"010203"

// Prepend to an empty ByteArray
let result2 = bytearray.push(#"", 0)
// result2 == #"00"
```

The signature is:
```aiken
pub fn push(self: ByteArray, byte: Byte) -> ByteArray
```
The byte is inserted at the **front** (index 0) of the `ByteArray`.

```aiken
use aiken/primitive/bytearray
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction}
use cardano/assets.{PolicyId}

validator nonce_check {
  mint(redeemer: ByteArray, _policy_id: PolicyId, _self: Transaction) -> Bool {
    let prefix =
      #""
        |> bytearray.push(0x00)
        |> bytearray.push(0xff)
    redeemer == prefix
  }
}
```

Here `bytearray.push(0x00)` gives `#"00"`, then `bytearray.push(0xff)` prepends `ff` to yield `#"ff00"`. The validator passes only when the redeemer equals that prefix.

