`maxTxExUnits` caps the total CPU steps and memory units a single transaction's Plutus scripts may consume (10,000,000,000 steps / 10,000,000 mem units). `maxBlockExUnits` applies the same cap across all scripts in a block (40,000,000,000 steps / 50,000,000 mem units). These limits prevent runaway script execution from stalling the network.

