- The refactored version uses `assets.flatten(self.mint)` to get all `(PolicyId, AssetName, Int)` triples from the mint field.
- It then filters to only the entries matching `policy_id` with `qty > 0`, ensuring at least one token under this policy is minted with a positive quantity.
