- The datum encodes what token the swap creator wants in return.
- The validator passes if either the owner themselves signs (to cancel the offer) or if any output in the transaction carries at least the required quantity of the specified token (fulfilling the swap).
- This mirrors the CIP-0118 swap use-case where an aggregator batches the sub-transaction with a fulfilling transaction.

